<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="7" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,1341,1692]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,325,1377,1404]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Discussion</emphasis>
. Both 
<taxonomicName authority="(Mohrig)" authorityName="Vilkamaa &amp; Menzel" authorityYear="2019" baseAuthorityName="Vilkamaa &amp; Menzel" baseAuthorityYear="2019" box="[407,647,1377,1404]" class="Insecta" family="Sciaridae" genus="Lycoriella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sordida" status="comb. n.">
<emphasis box="[407,534,1377,1403]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Br. sordida</emphasis>
(Mohrig)
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[657,763,1378,1404]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[657,763,1378,1404]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" rank="species">comb. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Mohrig &amp; Krivosheina)" authorityName="Vilkamaa &amp; Menzel" authorityYear="2019" baseAuthorityName="Mohrig &amp; Krivosheina" baseAuthorityYear="2019" box="[824,1265,1377,1404]" class="Insecta" family="Sciaridae" genus="Lycoriella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dearmata" status="comb. n.">
<emphasis box="[824,973,1377,1403]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Br. dearmata</emphasis>
(Mohrig &amp; Krivosheina)
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1276,1381,1378,1404]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1276,1381,1378,1404]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" rank="species">comb. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
(see above) are placed in the genus 
<emphasis box="[500,651,1413,1439]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Tuomikoski. In" authorityYear="1960" box="[500,647,1413,1439]" class="Insecta" family="Sciaridae" genus="Bradysiopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Bradysiopsis</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
in the here newly established 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Vilkamaa &amp; Menzel" authorityYear="2019" baseAuthorityName="Mohrig &amp; Krivosheina" baseAuthorityYear="2019" box="[993,1139,1413,1439]" class="Insecta" family="Sciaridae" genus="Lycoriella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dearmata">
<emphasis box="[993,1139,1413,1439]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Br. dearmata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group. Both species have, unlike the 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Meigen" baseAuthorityYear="1830" box="[272,384,1450,1475]" class="Insecta" family="Sciaridae" genus="Bradysiopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vittata">
<emphasis box="[272,384,1450,1475]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Br. vittata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Mohrig &amp; Mamaev" baseAuthorityYear="1970" box="[515,658,1449,1475]" class="Insecta" family="Sciaridae" genus="Bradysiopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="disjuncta">
<emphasis box="[515,658,1449,1475]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Br. disjuncta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group, a distinctly bordered patch of sensilla on the first palpal segment, conically narrowed and apically roundish tegmen, elongate-ovale gonostylus with the apex which is curved to the medial side and—like in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Menzel &amp; Mohrig" authorityYear="1998" box="[505,695,1521,1547]" class="Insecta" family="Sciaridae" genus="Pseudolycoriella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[505,695,1521,1547]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Pseudolycoriella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
—densely setose, and which reaches apicad from the apical tooth. With their long three-segmented palpus, four strong setae on scutellum, untoothed tarsal claws, partly bow-like bordered and densely setose tibial organ, the lack of a whiplash seta on the gonostylus, the 2–3 long setae on the medial side of the gonostylus and a slender apical tooth in combination with three subapical megasetae, both species possess typical 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Tuomikoski. In" authorityYear="1960" box="[325,470,1665,1691]" class="Insecta" family="Sciaridae" genus="Bradysiopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[325,470,1665,1691]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Bradysiopsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
characters [compare with the genus diagnosis in 
<bibRefCitation author="Menzel, F. &amp; Mohrig, W." box="[1022,1369,1665,1692]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" refId="ref43072" refString="Menzel, F. &amp; Mohrig, W. (2000) Revision der palaarktischen Trauermucken (Diptera: Sciaridae). Studia dipterologica Supplement, 6 (1999). Ampyx-Verlag, Halle (Saale), 761 pp." type="book" year="2000">Menzel &amp; Mohrig (2000: 185)</bibRefCitation>
].
</paragraph>
